# NOTE: README.md is NOT ignored — the test stage's QA gate
# (test_docs_present_and_current) reads it. The runtime stage copies app files
# explicitly (config.py db.py app.py … web/), so README never ships anyway.
# NOTE: tests/, pytest.ini, requirements-dev.txt are intentionally NOT ignored —
# the Docker "test" stage runs the full QA suite on every build (build fails on
# regression). The runtime stage copies only app files, so the final image stays
# clean and never ships the tests.
